Sr. QA Automation Engineer 

We're currently looking for a great talented Sr. QA Engineer who should join our team. 

Primary responsibilities:
• Design and executive test plans for all built in-house apps (websites, desktop and mobile apps plus web services).
• Record and document results and compare to expected results.
• Detect software failures so that defects may be discovered and corrected.
• Generate historical analysis of test results.
• Develop and document application test plans based on software requirements and technical specifications.
• Perform application security and performance audits.
• Determining and agreeing in-house quality procedures, standards and/or specifications.
• Produce clear and accurate bug reports, test reports and test plans
• Work independently as well as part of a team 
• Provide feedback on development processes and contribute to improvement of these processes


Required Skills/Experience: 
• Experience of system testing of client and server applications.
• Hands on experience with JUnit, Selenium, SoapUI or RESTClient
• Be an expert in Test Automation.
• 5+ years of relevant QA technical experience.
• 3+ years large enterprise or e-business systems experience.
• Ability to understand and create test plans from specifications or verbal communications.
• Dynamic, proactive, and with excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Analyze, design, author and execute new or modified tests to high quality
• Problem solver skills
• Documents and demonstrates solutions by developing documentation, flowcharts, layouts, diagrams, charts, code comments and clear code.
• To ensure that the products and services the company provides are of the highest possible quality in terms of build, performance, customer expectations and statutory requirements. 
• To monitor and advise on the performance of the quality management system and produces data and report on performance, measuring against set indicators. 
• Setting QA compliance objectives and ensuring that targets are achieved;

Highly Desirable:
• Experience of server side technologies: Java (or any other programming language), SQL, web services
• See things from a customers point of view and understand the business impact of bugs and features
• Demonstrate an understanding of different software test processes and methodologies

If you are interested, please send an email to hr@nobelglobe.com
